## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["🎤 Microphone"] --> B["SoX Recorder<br/>(voiceRecorder.ts)"]
    B --> C["WAV File (16kHz, mono)"]
    C --> D["Python Sidecar<br/>(stt_service.py)"]
    
    D --> E["Silero VAD<br/>(Voice Activity Detection)"]
    E -->|"No speech"| F["Return empty"]
    E -->|"Speech detected"| G["Vosk Streaming<br/>(Fast ~100ms)"]
    
    G --> H["Whisper Small<br/>(Accurate ~500ms)"]
    
    H --> I["JSON Result"]
    I --> J["Command Parser<br/>(commandParser.ts)"]
    J --> K["VS Code Controller<br/>(vscodeController.ts)"]
    K --> L["Editor Action"]
    
    J --> M["AI Engine<br/>(aiEngine.ts)"]
    M --> K
    
    K --> N["Voice Feedback<br/>(voiceFeedback.ts)"]
    N --> O["🔊 Speaker"]
    
    P["Wake Word Detector<br/>(wakeWordDetector.ts)"] --> Q["Mode Manager<br/>(voiceModeManager.ts)"]
    Q --> B
```

### Pipeline Flow

```
Microphone Input
      ↓
SoX Recording (16kHz WAV)
      ↓
Silero VAD (silence detection)
      ↓
Vosk Streaming Recognition (~100ms)
      ↓
Whisper Small Transcription (~500ms)
      ↓
Command Parser (regex matching)
      ↓
VS Code Extension Controller
      ↓
Editor Action + Voice Feedback
```

---

## Hybrid Speech Pipeline

### Why Hybrid Vosk + Whisper?

| Feature | Vosk | Whisper Small |
|---------|------|---------------|
| **Speed** | ~100ms | ~500ms |
| **Accuracy** | Good | Excellent |
| **Indian English** | Moderate | Very Good |
| **Offline** | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes |
| **Model Size** | ~40MB | ~244MB |
| **Use Case** | Wake-word detection | Command transcription |

### Pipeline Modes

**PASSIVE Mode** (Wake-word detection):
1. Record 3-second clip
2. Silero VAD checks for speech → skip if silent
3. Vosk processes audio (fast, ~100ms)
4. If potential wake word detected → verify with Whisper
5. Result: Fast wake-word detection with low latency

**ACTIVE Mode** (Command processing):
1. Record 7-second clip
2. Silero VAD checks for speech → skip if silent
3. Vosk processes audio (quick reference)
4. Whisper Small processes audio (primary result)
5. Result: Accurate command transcription

### Indian English Accent Support

The system uses Whisper Small specifically for Indian English because:
- Whisper was trained on 680,000 hours of multilingual audio
- The `small` model (244M parameters) handles accent variation well
- We force `language="en"` to prevent Hindi/Hinglish confusion
- The `initial_prompt` primes the model for coding vocabulary
- Vosk provides a fast backup for simple commands

