## Language Detection

The assistant automatically detects the programming language from the file extension:

| Extension | Language | Priority |
|-----------|----------|----------|
| [.py](file:///d:/assistant/voice-coding-assistant/src/stt_service.py) | Python | ⭐ Primary |
| `.java` | Java | ⭐ Primary |
| `.js` | JavaScript | Supported |
| [.ts](file:///d:/assistant/voice-coding-assistant/src/aiEngine.ts) | TypeScript | Supported |
| `.cpp` / `.cc` | C++ | Supported |
| `.c` / `.h` | C | Supported |
| `.go` | Go | Supported |
| `.rs` | Rust | Supported |
| `.rb` | Ruby | Supported |
| `.php` | PHP | Supported |
| `.cs` | C# | Supported |
| `.kt` | Kotlin | Supported |
| `.swift` | Swift | Supported |

### How Language Detection Works

```
User says: "create function add numbers"

If file is calculator.py → Python syntax:
    def add_numbers(a, b):
        return a + b

If file is Calculator.java → Java syntax:
    public int addNumbers(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }

If file is calculator.js → JavaScript syntax:
    function addNumbers(a, b) {
        return a + b;
    }
```

